    This class acts as a container for the set of properties representing a software release that are read from a manifest:
    • A build timestamp: see getBuildTimestamp() / setBuildTimestamp(java.lang.Long)
    • A version identifier: see getVersion() / setVersion(java.lang.String)
    • An SCM revision identifier: see getRevision() / setRevision(java.lang.String)
    In addition, utility readFromManifest(java.lang.Class<?>) method provides a way to read manifest attributes into a SoftwareReleaseProperties object.

        public static SoftwareReleaseProperties readFromManifest(Class<?> clazz)
        Reads a SoftwareReleaseProperties object from the manifest in the Jar containing the given class.

        The mapping between Jar manifest attributes and software release properties is as follows:
        • Version identifier: Implementation-Version
        • Build timestamp: Build-Timestamp
        • SCM revision identifier: Implementation-Revision
        If an attribute cannot be read from the Jar's manifest or if its value cannot be converted to the right datatype, then the null value is used for the corresponding property. If the Jar does not contain a manifest, or if the given class does not exist or was not loaded from a Jar, null values are used for all three properties.
